{"key":"post-13497159","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13497159</id>\n<content>After mixing the water and vermiculite, there should&amp;nbsp; be &lt;i&gt;zero water&lt;/i&gt; in the bottom of the bowl before adding the rice flour.&amp;nbsp; If there is, colonization will be very slow and this in turn opens the door for contaminants.&amp;nbsp; Wet substrates colonize slow if at all, while substrates on the dry side colonize very fast.&amp;nbsp; You're going to dunk before first flush to add the water for fruiting, so there's no need to get it too wet before inoculation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;All of this is covered in detail for visual learners in the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;brf tek video&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13497173</next>\n<prev>13496727</prev>\n<first>13496266</first>\n<last>13497202</last>\n<when>1290010788</when>\n<utime>11/17/10 06:19 PM</utime>\n</post>"}